obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (18901)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, application and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=18901&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Government`
  line `Securities Act, 2006.`
  line
  line `(2) This Act applies to Government securities created and issued whether before or after the`
  line `commencement of this Act by the Central Government or a State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) It applies in the first instance to whole of the States, except the State of Jammu and Kashmir, and`
  line `to all the Union territories and it shall also apply to the State of Jammu and Kashmir which adopts this`
  line `Act by resolution passed in that behalf under clause (1) of article 252 of the Constitution.`
  line
  line `(4) It shall come into force in all the States, except the State of Jammu and Kashmir, and in the Union`
  line `territories on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint`
  line `and in the State of Jammu and Kashmir which adopts this Act under clause (1) of article 252 of the`
  line `Constitution, on the date of such adoption; and any reference in this Act to the commencement of this Act`
  line `shall, in relation to any State or Union territory, means the date on which this Act, comes into force in`
  line `such State or Union territory.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 30th November, 2007, vide notification no. S.O. 2020, dated 1st December, 2007, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (18902)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=18902&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "agent" means a scheduled bank within the meaning of clause (e) of section 2 of the Reserve`
  line `Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934), or any other person specified as such;`
  line
  line `(b) "Bank" means the Reserve Bank of India constituted under section 3 of the Reserve Bank of`
  line `India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line
  line `(c) "bond ledger account" means an account with the Bank or an agent in which the Government`
  line `securities are held in a dematerialised form at the credit of the holder;`
  line
  line `(d) "constituents' subsidiary general ledger account" means a subsidiary general ledger account`
  line `opened and maintained with the Bank by an agent on behalf of the constituents of such agent;`
  line
  line `(e) "Government", in relation to any Government security, means the Central or State`
  line `Government issuing the security;`
  line
  line `(f) "Government security" means a security created and issued by the Government for the purpose`
  line `of raising a public loan or for any other purpose as may be notified by the Government in the Official`
  line `Gazette and having one of the forms mentioned in section 3;`
  line
  line `(g) "prescribed" means prescribed by regulations made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) "promissory note" includes a treasury bill;`
  line
  line `(i) "specified" means specified by the Bank in the Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (18903)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Forms of Government securities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=18903&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `A Government security may, subject to such terms and`
  line `conditions as may be specified, be in such forms as may be prescribed or in one of the following forms,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) a Government promissory note payable to or to the order of a certain persons; or`
  line
  line `(ii) a bearer bond payable to bearer; or`
  line
  line `(iii) a stock; or`
  line
  line `(iv) a bond held in a bond ledger account.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this section, "stock" means a Government security,--`
  line
  line `(i) registered in the books of the Bank for which a stock certificate is issued; or`
  line
  line `(ii) held at the credit of the holder in the subsidiary general ledger account including the`
  line `constituents subsidiary general ledger account maintained in the books of the Bank,`
  line
  line `and transferable by registration in the books of the Bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (18904)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Subsidiary general ledger account.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=18904&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) A subsidiary general ledger account including a`
  line `constituents' subsidiary general ledger account and a bond ledger account may be opened and maintained`
  line `by the Bank subject to such conditions and restrictions as may be specified and in such form and on`
  line `payment of such fee as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Benami Transactions (Prohibition) Act, 1988 (45 of`
  line `1988), or any other law for the time being in force, the Government securities may be held on behalf of a`
  line `constituent in a constituents' subsidiary general ledger account under sub-section (1) and the holder of`
  line `such account shall be deemed to be the holder of the securities held in that account:`
  line
  line `Provided that the constituent as a beneficial owner of the Government security shall be entitled to`
  line `claim from the holder all the benefits and be subjected to all the liabilities in respect of the Government`
  line `securities held in the constituents' subsidiary general ledger account.`
  line
  line `(3) The holder of a constituents' subsidiary general ledger account shall maintain such records and`
  line `adopt such procedure for safeguarding the interests of the constituents as may be specified.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (18905)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Transfer of Government securities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=18905&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) No transfer of a Government security shall be valid if it`
  line `does not purport to convey the full title to the security.`
  line
  line `(2) The transfer of the Government securities shall be made in such form and in such manner as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Any document relating to a Government security or any endorsement on a promissory note issued`
  line `by the Government may, on the demand of a person who for any reason is unable to write, shall be`
  line `executed on his behalf in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in this section shall affect any order made by the Bank under this Act, or any order made`
  line `by a Court upon the Bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (18906)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Holding of Government securities by holders of public offices.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=18906&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the case of any public`
  line `office to which the Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare this sub-section to`
  line `apply, a Government security may be held in the name of the office.`
  line
  line `(2) When a Government security is so held, it shall be deemed to be transferred without any or further`
  line `endorsement or transfer deed from each holder of the office to the succeeding holder of the office on and`
  line `from the date on which the latter takes charge of the office.`
  line
  line `(3) When the holder of the office transfers to a party not being his successor in office where a`
  line `Government security so held, the transfer shall be made by the signature of the holder of the office and`
  line `the name of the office in the manner laid down in section 5.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the holder of the office is temporarily absent for more than a fortnight from his office for`
  line `any reason, he may authorise in writing such other person, who would be incharge of this office during`
  line `the period of such absence, to effect transfer of the Government securities.`
  line
  line `(5) This section applies as well to an office of which there are two or more joint holders as to an`
  line `office of which there is a single holder.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (18907)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Recognition of title to Government security of deceased sole holder or joint holders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=18907&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of sub-sections (2) and (3), if on the death of a sole holder or death of all the`
  line `joint holders of a Government security there is no nomination in force, the executors or administrators of`
  line `the deceased sole holder or all the deceased joint holders, as the case may be, or the holder of a succession`
  line `certificate issued under Part X of the Indian Succession Act, 1925 (39 of 1925) shall be the only person`
  line `who may be recognised by the Bank as having any title to the Government security.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in this section shall bar the recognition by the Bank of any person as having a`
  line `title to a Government security on the basis of a decree, order or direction passed by a competent court`
  line `declaring the person as having title to the Government security or appointing a receiver to take possession`
  line `of a security or on the basis of a certificate issued or order passed by any other authority who might have`
  line `been empowered under any statute to confer on any such person a title to the Government security or on`
  line `the basis of such other documents as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section or in any other law for the time being in force,`
  line `where the outstanding value of Government security held by a deceased sole holder or deceased joint`
  line `holders, as the case may be, does not exceed an amount of rupees one lakh or such higher amount not`
  line `exceeding rupees one crore as may be fixed by the Central Government by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette from time to time, the Bank may recognise a person as having title to such Government security`
  line `of the deceased sole holder or deceased joint holders in such manner and subject to such conditions as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (18908)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Right of survivors of joint holders or several payees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=18908&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `section 45 of the Indian Contract Act, 1872 (9 of 1872) and subject to the provisions of sections 7 and`
  line 10,--
  line
  line `(a) when a Government security is held by two or more persons jointly, and either or any of them`
  line `dies, the title to the Government security shall vest in the survivor or survivors of those persons; and`
  line
  line `(b) when a Government security is payable to two or more persons severally and either or any of`
  line `them dies, the Government security shall be payable to the survivor or survivors of those persons or`
  line `to the representative of the deceased or to any one of them:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall affect any claim which any representative of a`
  line `deceased joint holder or deceased holders of a Government security or a surviving joint holder or holders`
  line `of a Government security, as the case may be, may have against the survivor or survivors or`
  line `representatives under or in respect of any Government security to which this section applies.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, a body incorporated or deemed to be incorporated`
  line `under the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), or the Co-operative Societies Act, 1912 (2 of 1912), or any`
  line `other enactment for the time being in force relating to the incorporation of associations of individuals,`
  line `shall be deemed to die when it is dissolved.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (18909)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Nomination by holders of Government securities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=18909&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `sections 7 and 8 or any other law for the time being in force, except the provisions of sub-section (2),--`
  line
  line `(a) where a Government security other than in the form of promissory note or bearer bond is held`
  line `by a person in his name or jointly with any other name or names, as the case may be, the sole holder`
  line `or all the joint holders of the Government security together may nominate one or more persons in`
  line `such form and in such manner as may be prescribed, who in the event of the death of the sole holder`
  line `or the death of all the joint holders, as the case may be, would become entitled to the Government`
  line `security and to payment thereon to the exclusion of all other persons, unless the nomination is varied`
  line `or cancelled in the prescribed manner;`
  line
  line `(b) where a nomination in respect of a Government security has been made in favour of two or`
  line `more nominees and either or any of them is dead, the surviving nominee or nominees, as the case may`
  line `be, shall be entitled to the Government security and payment thereon;`
  line
  line `(c) where the nominee is a minor, it shall be lawful for the sole holder or all the joint holders of a`
  line `Government security, as the case may be, to appoint in the prescribed manner any person in whom the`
  line `Government security would be deemed to have vested in the event of death of such holder or joint`
  line `holders of the Government security during the minority of the nominee;`
  line
  line `(d) the recognition of right and claim of the nominee or nominees to the Government security`
  line `held by a sole holder or joint holders, as the case may be, and any payment made by the Government`
  line `or the Bank to the nominee or nominees shall constitute a full discharge and shall absolve the`
  line `Government or the Bank of its liability in respect of the said Government security.`
  line
  line `(2) Any nomination or appointment made under sub-section (1) shall become void if the nominee`
  line `predeceases, or where there are two or more nominees, if all the nominees predecease the holder or joint`
  line `holders of the Government security making the nomination.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the amount due for the time being on a Government security is payable to two or more`
  line `nominees and either or any of them dies, the title to the Government security shall vest in the survivor or`
  line `survivors of those nominees and the amount for the time being due thereon shall be paid accordingly.`
  line
  line `(4) A transfer of a Government security made in accordance with sub-section (2) of section 5 shall`
  line `automatically cancel the nomination previously made:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a Government security is in the possession of a person either as a pledge or by`
  line `way of security for any purpose, such possession shall not have the effect of cancelling the nomination,`
  line `but the right of the nominee shall be subject to the right of the person so possessing it.`
  line
  line `(5) The Government may, on the recommendation of the Bank, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `extend the facility of nomination to any Government security as may be specified therein.`
  line
  line `(6) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall affect the right or claim which any person may have`
  line `against the person whose right and title to a Government security is recognised by the Government or the`
  line `Bank or to whom the payment of the amount due on the Government security is made by the Government`
  line `or the Bank under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(7) No notice of any claim of any person, other than the person or persons in whose name a`
  line `Government security is held or the nominees thereof, shall be receivable by the Bank or the Government,`
  line `nor shall the Bank or the Government be bound by any such notice even though expressly given to it:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any decree, order, certificate or other authority from a court of competent`
  line `jurisdiction relating to such Government security is produced before the Bank or the Government, the`
  line `Bank or the Government shall take due note of such decree, order, certificate or other authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (18910)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Government securities belonging to minor or insane person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=18910&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any Government`
  line `security is held on behalf of a minor, the payment of the same for the time being due on a Government`
  line `security either by way of outstanding principal or interest thereon may be made to the father or mother of`
  line `such minor and where neither parent is alive or where the living parents are or only living parent is`
  line `incapable of action, to a person entitled under the law for the time being in force to have care of the`
  line `property of the minor.`
  line
  line `(2) When a Government security belongs to a minor or a person who is insane and incapable of`
  line `managing his affairs and the outstanding principal value of the Government security does not in the`
  line `aggregate exceed rupees one lakh or such higher amount not exceeding rupees one crore as the Central`
  line `Government may, by a notification in the Official Gazette from time to time, fix, the Bank may make`
  line `such order as it thinks fit for the vesting of such Government security in such person as it considers`
  line `represents the minor or insane person.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (18911)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Issue of duplicate securities and of new securities on conversion, consolidation, sub-division, renewal, stripping or reconstruction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=18911&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the person entitled to a Government security applies to the`
  line `Bank alleging that the Government security has been lost, stolen or destroyed, or has been defaced or`
  line `mutilated, the Bank may, on proof to its satisfaction of the loss, theft, destruction, defacement or`
  line `mutilation of the Government security, and subject to such conditions and on payment of such fees as`
  line `may be prescribed, order the issue of a duplicate Government security to the applicant.`
  line
  line `(2) If the person entitled to a Government security applies to the Bank to have the Government`
  line `security converted into a Government security of another form, or into a Government security issued in`
  line `connection with another loan or to have it consolidated with other like Government securities, or to have`
  line `it sub-divided, or to have it renewed, stripped or reconstituted, the Bank may, subject to such conditions`
  line `and on payment of such fees as may be prescribed, cancel the Government security and order the issue of`
  line `a new Government security or Government securities.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--A Government security may be stripped separately for interest and principal or`
  line `reconstituted on the application of the holder subject to such terms and conditions as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(3) The person to whom a duplicate Government security or a new Government security is issued`
  line `under this section shall be deemed for the purposes of section 18 to have been recognised by the Bank as`
  line `the holder of the Government security; and a duplicate Government security or new Government security`
  line `so issued to any person shall be deemed to constitute a new contract between the Government and such`
  line `person and all persons deriving title thereafter through him:`
  line
  line `Provided that the issue of new security under this section shall not affect the interest of third parties in`
  line `whose favour a charge or other interest was lawfully created and was subsisting at the time of issue of the`
  line `new security.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (18912)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Summary determination by Bank of title to Government security in case of dispute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=18912&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) If`
  line `the Bank is of opinion that a doubt exists as to the title to a Government security, it may proceed to`
  line `determine, in accordance with such regulations as may be made, the person who shall for the purposes of`
  line `the Bank be deemed to be the person entitled thereto.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of making any order which it is empowered to make under this Act, the Bank may`
  line `request a District Magistrate to record or to have recorded the whole or any part of such evidence as any`
  line `person whose evidence the Bank requires may produce and the District Magistrate so requested may`
  line `either himself record, or may direct any Executive Magistrate empowered in this behalf by general or special order of the State Government to record the evidence, and shall forward a copy thereof to the`
  line Bank.
  line
  line `(3) For the purpose of making a vesting order under this Act, the Bank may direct one of its officers`
  line `to record the evidence of any person whose evidence the Bank requires or may receive evidence upon`
  line affidavit.
  line
  line `(4) A Magistrate or an officer of the Bank acting in pursuance of this section may administer an oath`
  line `to any witness examined by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (18913)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Law applicable in regard to Government securities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=18913&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding that as a matter of`
  line `convenience, the Government may have arranged for payments on a Government security to be made`
  line `elsewhere than in India, the rights of all persons in relation to Government securities shall be determined`
  line `in connection with all such questions as are dealt with by this Act by the law and in the Courts of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (18914)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Postponement of payments and registration of transfers pending the making of vesting order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=18914&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Where the Bank contemplates making an order under this Act to vest a Government security in`
  line `any person, the Bank may suspend payment of interest on or the maturity value of the Government`
  line `security or postpone the making of any order under section 7, section 10, section 11 or section 12 or the`
  line `registration of any transfer of the Government security, as the case may be, until the vesting order has`
  line `been made.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (18915)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Power of Bank to require bonds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=18915&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Before making any order which it is empowered to make`
  line `under this Act, the Bank may require the person in whose favour the order is to be made to execute an`
  line `indemnity bond with one or more sureties in such form as may be prescribed or to furnish security not`
  line `exceeding twice the value of the subject-matter of the order, to be held at the disposal of the Bank, to pay`
  line `to the Bank or any person to whom the Bank may assign the indemnity bond or security in furtherance of`
  line `sub-section (2) the amount thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) A Court before which a claim in respect of the subject-matter of any such order is established may`
  line `order the indemnity bond or security to be assigned to the successful claimant who shall thereupon be`
  line `entitled to enforce the indemnity bond or realise the security to the extent of such claim.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (18916)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Publication of notices in Official Gazette.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=18916&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Any notice required to be given by the Bank under`
  line `this Act may be served by post, but every such notice shall also be published by the Bank in the Official`
  line `Gazette or the Official Gazette of a State, according as the notice relates to a Government security, issued`
  line `by the Central Government or a State Government, and on such publication shall be deemed to have been`
  line `delivered to all persons for whom it is intended.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (18917)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Procedure and scope of vesting order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=18917&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Bank shall, while making a vesting order under`
  line `section 7, section 10, section 11 or section 12, follow such procedure as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) An order made by the Bank under this Act may either confer full title to a Government security or`
  line `a title only to the accrued and accruing interest on the Government security pending a further order`
  line `vesting full title.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (18918)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Legal effect of orders made by Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=18918&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `No recognition by the Bank of a person as the holder of`
  line `a Government security, and no order made by the Bank under this Act shall be called in question by any`
  line `Court so far as such recognition or order affects the relations of the Government or the Bank with the`
  line `person recognised by the Bank as the holder of a Government security or with any person claiming an`
  line `interest in such security; and any such recognition by the Bank of any person or any order by the Bank`
  line `vesting a Government security in any person shall operate to confer on that person a title to the security`
  line `subject only to his personal liability to the rightful owner of the security for money had and received on`
  line `his account.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (18919)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Stay of proceedings on order of Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=18919&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Where the Bank contemplates making with reference`
  line `to any Government security any order which it is empowered to make under this Act, and before the order is made the Bank receives from a Court in India an order to stay the making of such order, the Bank shall`
  line either--
  line
  line `(a) hold the security together with any interest unpaid or accruing thereon until further orders of`
  line `the Court are received; or`
  line
  line `(b) apply to the Court to have the security transferred to the Official Trustees appointed for the`
  line `State in which such Court is situated, pending the disposal of the proceedings before the Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (18920)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Cancellation by Bank of vesting proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=18920&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Where the Bank contemplates making an order`
  line `under this Act vesting a Government security in any person, the Bank may, at any time before the order is`
  line `made, cancel any proceedings already taken for that purpose and may, on such cancellation, proceed anew`
  line `to the making of such order.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (18921)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Discharge in respect of interest on Government securities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=18921&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise expressly`
  line `provided in the terms of a Government security, no person shall be entitled to claim interest on such`
  line `security in respect of any period which has elapsed after the earliest date on which demand could have`
  line `been made for the payment of the amount due on such security.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (18922)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Discharge in respect of bearer bonds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=18922&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The Government shall be discharged from all liability`
  line `on a bearer bond or on any interest coupon of such a bond on payment to the holder of such bond or`
  line `coupon on presentation on or after the date when it becomes due of the amount expressed therein, unless`
  line `before such payment, an order of a Court in India has been served on the Government restraining it from`
  line `making payment.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (18923)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Period of limitation of Governments’ liability in respect of interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=18923&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where no shorter`
  line `period of limitation is fixed by any law for the time being in force, the liability of the Government in`
  line `respect of any interest payment due on a Government security shall terminate on the expiry of six years`
  line `from the date on which the amount due by way of interest became payable:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Government may allow a bona fide claim for payment of interest after the expiry of`
  line `the period of six years in those cases where the holders of securities could not prefer their claims within`
  line `the said period of six years.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Bank may specify the securities in`
  line `respect of which, the circumstances under which, and the terms and conditions subject to which, interest`
  line `may be paid even after the expiry of the period specified in the said sub-section.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (18924)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Inspection of documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=18924&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `No person shall be entitled to inspect or to receive information`
  line `derived from any Government security in the possession or custody of the Government or from any book,`
  line `register or other document kept or maintained by or on behalf of the Government in relation to`
  line `Government securities or any Government security, save in such circumstances and manner and subject to`
  line `such conditions as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (18925)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Micro films, facsimile copies of documents, magnetic tapes and computer print outs as documents of evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=18925&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in`
  line force,--
  line
  line `(a) a micro film of a document or the reproduction of the image or images embodied in such`
  line `micro film (whether enlarged or not); or`
  line
  line `(b) a facsimile copy of a document; or`
  line
  line `(c) a statement contained in a document and included in a printed material produced by a`
  line `computer, magnetic tape or any other form of mechanical or electronic data retrieval mechanism`
  line `(hereinafter referred to as computer print out), if the conditions mentioned in sub-section (2) and the`
  line `other provisions contained in this section are satisfied in relation to the statement and the computer in`
  line question,
  line
  line `shall be deemed to be also a document for the purposes of this Act and the regulations made thereunder`
  line `and shall be admissible in any proceedings thereunder, without further proof or production of the original,`
  line `as evidence of any contents of the original or of any fact stated therein of which direct evidence would be`
  line admissible.
  line
  line `(2) The conditions referred to in sub-section (1) in respect of a computer print out shall be the`
  line `following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the computer print out containing the statement was produced by the computer during the`
  line `period over which the computer was used regularly to store or process information for the purposes of`
  line `any activities regularly carried on over that period by the person having lawful control over the use of`
  line `the computer;`
  line
  line `(b) during the said period, there was regularly supplied to the computer in the ordinary course of`
  line `the said activities, information of the kind contained in the statement or of the kind from which the`
  line `information so contained is derived;`
  line
  line `(c) throughout the material part of the said period, the computer was operating properly or, if not,`
  line `then any respect in which it was not operating properly or was out of operation during that part of that`
  line `period was not such as to affect the production of the document or the accuracy of the contents; and`
  line
  line `(d) the information contained in the statement reproduced or is derived from information supplied`
  line `to the computer in the ordinary course of the said activities.`
  line
  line `(3) Where over any period, the function of storing or processing information for the purposes of any`
  line `activities regularly carried on over that period as mentioned in clause (a) of sub-section (2) was regularly`
  line `performed by computers, whether--`
  line
  line `(a) by a combination of computers operating over that period; or`
  line
  line `(b) by different computers operating in succession over that period; or`
  line
  line `(c) by different combinations of computers operating in succession over that period; or`
  line
  line `(d) in any other manner involving the successive operation over that period, in whatever order, of`
  line `one or more computers and one or more combinations of computers,`
  line
  line `all the computers used for that purpose during that period shall be treated for the purposes of this section`
  line `as constituting a single computer; and references in this section to a computer shall be construed`
  line accordingly.
  line
  line `(4) In any proceeding under this Act and the regulations made thereunder where it is desired to give a`
  line `statement in evidence by virtue of this section, a certificate doing any of the following things, that is to`
  line say,--
  line
  line `(a) identifying the document containing the statement and describing the manner in which it was`
  line produced;
  line
  line `(b) giving such particulars of any device involved in the production of that document as may be`
  line `appropriate for the purpose of showing that the document was produced by a computer;`
  line
  line `(c) dealing with any of the matters to which the conditions mentioned in sub-section (2) relate,`
  line `and purporting to be signed by a person occupying a responsible official position in the Bank in`
  line `relation to the operation of the relevant device or the management of the relevant activities`
  line `(whichever is appropriate),`
  line
  line `shall be evidence of any matter stated in the certificate; and for the purposes of this sub-section it shall be`
  line `sufficient for a matter to be stated to the best of the knowledge and belief of the person stating it.`
  line
  line `(5) For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) information shall be taken to be supplied to a computer if it is supplied thereto in any`
  line `appropriate form and whether it is so supplied directly or (with or without human intervention) by`
  line `means of any appropriate equipment;`
  line
  line `(b) whether in the course of activities carried on by any official, information is supplied with a`
  line `view to its being stored or processed for the purposes of those activities by a computer operated`
  line `otherwise than in the course of those activities, that information, if duly supplied to that computer,`
  line `shall be taken to be supplied to it in the course of those activities;`
  line
  line `(c) a document shall be taken to have been produced by a computer whether it was produced by it`
  line `directly or (with or without human intervention) by means of any appropriate equipment.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "computer" means any electronic, magnetic, optical or other high-speed data processing`
  line `service device or system which performs logical, arithmetical and memory functions by manipulation`
  line `of electronic, magnetic or optical impulses and includes all input, output, processing, storage,`
  line `computer software or communication facilities which are connected or related to the computer in a`
  line `computer system or computer network;`
  line
  line `(b) "computer print out" shall include ledgers, day-books, account books and other records,`
  line `maintained in the ordinary course of business of the Bank or of the agent, printed on paper from the`
  line `information stored in the computer or derived from such information; and`
  line
  line `(c) any reference to information being derived from other information shall be a reference to its`
  line `being derived therefrom by calculation, comparison or any other process.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (18926)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Bank and its officers to be public officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=18926&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of section 124 of the Indian`
  line `Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872), the provisions of Part IV of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of`
  line `1908) relating to suits by or against public officers in their official capacity, and the provisions of rule 27`
  line `of Order V, and rule 52 of Order XXI of the said Code, the Bank and any officer of the Bank acting in his`
  line `capacity as such shall be deemed to be a public officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (18927)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Misuse of subsidiary general ledger account facility.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=18927&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Where a subsidiary general ledger`
  line `account is opened by the Bank in favour of any holder of a Government security in terms of section 4`
  line and,--
  line
  line `(a) it comes to the notice of the Bank that the said account is being operated contrary to the terms`
  line `and conditions subject to which the account was opened; or`
  line
  line `(b) the subsidiary general ledger account transfer form has bounced due to insufficiency of`
  line `Government security or funds; or`
  line
  line `(c) the Bank is of opinion that the account is being operated contrary to the banking practice or in`
  line `a manner prejudicial to the interests of the holders of Government securities in general; or`
  line
  line `(d) the subsidiary general ledger account is being misused in any manner,`
  line
  line `the Bank may, by order in writing, after giving an opportunity of being heard, debar the holder of such`
  line `account from trading with the subsidiary general ledger account facility temporarily or permanently as it`
  line `deems fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (18928)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Pledge, hypothecation or lien.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=18928&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to such terms and conditions as may be prescribed,`
  line `the holder of a Government security may create a pledge or hypothecation or lien in respect of such`
  line security.
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of notice of pledge or hypothecation or lien from the holder of the Government`
  line `security, the Bank or any agent maintaining the account in respect of such security shall make necessary entry in its record and such entry shall be evidence of the pledge, hypothecation or lien thereof, as the`
  line `case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (18929)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Power to call for information, cause inspection and issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=18929&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Bank may at`
  line `any time, for the purposes of this Act, call for such information as it deems necessary in relation to a`
  line `Government security from any agent, or holder of subsidiary general ledger account including`
  line `constituents subsidiary general ledger account and cause an inspection or scrutiny to be made by one or`
  line `more of its officers or other persons, of any agent or holder of a subsidiary general ledger account`
  line `including constituents subsidiary general ledger account.`
  line
  line `(2) The Bank may, if it considers necessary so to do, issue such directions as it thinks fit, in relation to`
  line `a Government security,--`
  line
  line `(i) to the holders of the subsidiary general ledger accounts including constituents' subsidiary`
  line `general ledger account;`
  line
  line `(ii) to the agents maintaining bond ledger account; and`
  line
  line `(iii) to any other person dealing with the Government securities,`
  line
  line `for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (18930)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Contravention and penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=18930&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person, for the purpose of obtaining for himself or for`
  line `any other person any title to a Government security, makes to any authority in any application made under this Act or in the course of any inquiry undertaken in pursuance of this Act any statement which is false`
  line `and which he either knows to be false or does not believe to be true, ^1[the Bank may impose a penalty not`
  line `exceeding five lakh rupees or twice the amount involved in such contravention, where the amount is`
  line `quantifiable, whichever is higher, and where such contravention is a continuing one, with a further`
  line `penalty, which may extend to five thousand rupees for every day after first day during which the`
  line `contravention continues].`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to any other action which the Bank may deem fit to take, the Bank, after giving`
  line `a reasonable opportunity of being heard, may impose on any person who contravenes any provision of`
  line `this Act, or contravenes any regulation, notification or direction issued under this Act, or violates the`
  line `terms and conditions for opening and maintenance of a subsidiary general ledger account, including`
  line `constituents’ subsidiary general ledger account, a penalty, not exceeding five lakh rupees and where such`
  line `contravention is a continuing one, further penalty which may extend to five thousand rupees for every day`
  line `after first day during which the contravention continues.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-12-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Sub-section (2) omitted by s. 2 and Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-12-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (18931)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Certain laws not to apply to Government securities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=18931&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Public Debt Act, 1944`
  line `(18 of 1944) shall cease to apply to the Government securities to which this Act applies and to all matters`
  line `for which provisions have been made by this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such cessation anything done or any action taken in the exercise of any power`
  line `conferred by or under that Act shall be deemed to have been done or taken in the exercise of the powers`
  line `conferred by or under this Act as if this Act was in force at all material times.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing contained in the Depositories Act, 1996 (22 of 1996) or the regulations made thereunder`
  line `shall apply to Government securities covered by this Act unless an agreement is executed to the contrary`
  line `by any depository under the Depositories Act, 1996 with the Government or the Bank, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31_a:
  sectionId (50604)
  sectionNo 31A
  orderNo 32
  title `Powers of Bank not to apply to International Financial Services Centre.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 50 of 2019, s. 33 and the second Schedule (w.e.f. 1-10-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=50604&sectionno=31A&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_31_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[31A. Powers of Bank not to apply to International Financial Services Centre.--`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, the powers exercisable`
  line `by the Bank under this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) shall not extend to an International Financial Services Centre set up under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 18 of the Special Economic Zones Act, 2005 (28 of 2005);`
  line
  line `(b) shall be exercisable by the International Financial Services Centre Authority established under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 4 of the International Financial Services Centres Authority Act, 2019,`
  line
  line `in so far as regulation of financial products, financial services and financial institutions that are permitted`
  line `in the International Financial Services Centres are concerned.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (18932)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 33
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273&sectionId=18932&sectionno=32&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00005_200638_1517807318273
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Bank may, with the previous approval of the Central`
  line `Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, make regulations to carry out the purposes of this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the form in which and the terms and conditions subject to which the Government securities`
  line `may be issued under section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) the form in which and the fee to be charged for opening and maintenance of subsidiary`
  line `general ledger account including constituents' subsidiary general ledger account and bond ledger`
  line `account by the Bank under sub-section (1) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(c) the form and manner in which Government securities shall be transferred under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 5 and the manner in which any document relating to any Government`
  line `security or any endorsement on a promissory note may be executed on behalf of a person who is`
  line `unable to write under sub-section (3) of that section;`
  line
  line `(d) the documents to be produced for recognition of title to the Government security of a`
  line `deceased sole holder or all deceased joint holders under sub-section (2) of section 7 and the manner in`
  line `which and the conditions subject to which the Bank may recognise title to a Government security`
  line `under sub-section (3) of that section;`
  line
  line `(e) the form and the manner in which a nomination may be made, varied or cancelled and the`
  line `manner in which any person may be appointed in whom the Government security would be deemed`
  line `to have vested in the event of death of holder or joint holders of Government security during the`
  line `minority of a nominee under section 9;`
  line
  line `(f) the conditions governing the issue of duplicate Government securities and the fees to be paid`
  line `therefor under section 11;`
  line
  line `(g) the manner in which the Bank may determine title to a Government security under section 12;`
  line
  line `(h) the form of bond under sub-section (1) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(i) the procedure for making vesting order referred to in sub-section (1) of section 17;`
  line
  line `(j) the circumstances and the manner in which and the conditions subject to which inspection of`
  line `Government securities, books, registers and other documents may be allowed or information`
  line `therefrom may be given under section 24;`
  line
  line `(k) the terms and conditions subject to which pledge or hypothecation or lien be created under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 28.`
  line
  line `(3) Every regulation made by the Bank under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made,`
  line `before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be`
  line `comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the regulation or both Houses agree that the regulation should not be made, the regulation`
  line `shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however,`
  line `that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously`
  line `done under that regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (18933)
  sectionNo (33)
